# Current Task Management

## Purpose
- Track the currently active development task
- Maintain focus on immediate objectives
- Provide clear context for ongoing work

## Structure Requirements
- Task title must be clear and specific
- Current status must be maintained
- Progress tracking must be included
- Next steps must be listed
- Dependencies must be documented

## Format Rules
1. Title section must start with "# Current Task:"
2. Status must be one of: "Not Started", "In Progress", "Blocked", "Ready for Review"
3. Progress must be tracked with checkboxes
4. Next steps must be numbered
5. All blockers must be documented with "!" prefix

## Sections
- Title (with task ID if applicable)
- Status
- Description
- Current Progress
- Next Steps
- Blockers (if any)
- Related Files
- Notes

## Usage Guidelines
1. Update at the start of each new task
2. Mark progress as items are completed
3. Document blockers immediately when encountered
4. Update status when transitioning between phases
5. Clear and reset when starting new task

## Example Format
```markdown
# Current Task: [Task Name]

## Status: [Current Status]

## Description
[Clear description of the task]

## Current Progress
- [ ] Step 1
- [x] Step 2
- [ ] Step 3

## Next Steps
1. [Next immediate action]
2. [Following action]
3. [Future action]

## Blockers
! [Blocker description if any]

## Related Files
- [File path 1]
- [File path 2]

## Notes
- [Important note 1]
- [Important note 2]
```

## Maintenance Rules
1. Keep the file focused on ONE task at a time
2. Update progress in real-time
3. Remove completed tasks before starting new ones
4. Document any task transitions
5. Reference relevant plan.md sections 